## 🔁 Suggested GitHub Practices

| Purpose        | Tool/Format                                                                             |
| -------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 📦 Package dev | [`nbdev`](https://nbdev.fast.ai/) (auto-generate modules + docs from notebooks)         |
| 🧪 CI/CD       | GitHub Actions to test `.py` files in `modules/` and perform `nbval` on key notebooks   |
| 🧾 Reports     | `nbconvert` or `jupyter nbconvert --to pdf/HTML` into `publications/nbconvert_outputs/` |
| 🌍 Site        | JupyterBook or Quarto site from `notebooks/` and `docs/` for publishing public views    |
| 🔬 Experiments | Maintain `experiments/` folder if you want ad-hoc exploratory notebooks                 |

---

## 🧠 Naming Shift Guidelines

Replace `CIv7` references across code, comments, and documentation with:

* `AlgoPlex` as the stable research platform name
* Specific submodule tags like `AlgoPlex-TI` for thematic intelligence or `AlgoPlex-SBD` for structural break detection
* Use semantic versioning for module maturity, e.g., `AlgoPlex-TI v1.1`

